   actions:"Multiattack. The beholder uses Eye Rays three times.\nBite. Melee Attack Roll: +8, reach 5 ft. Hit: 13 (3d6+3) Piercing damage.\nEye Rays. The beholder shoots one of the following magical rays at a target within 120 feet (roll 1d10, reroll if already used this turn):\n1: Charm Ray — WIS DC 16. Failure: 13 (3d8) Psychic, Charmed 1 hour.\n2: Paralyzing Ray — CON DC 16. Failure: Paralyzed (auto-succeed after 1 min).\n3: Fear Ray — WIS DC 16. Failure: 14 (4d6) Psychic, Frightened.\n4: Slowing Ray — CON DC 16. Failure: 18 (4d8) Necrotic, Speed halved.\n5: Enervation Ray — DEX DC 16. Failure: 36 (8d8) Necrotic.\n6: Telekinetic Ray — STR DC 16. Failure: Moved 30 ft, Restrained.\n7: Sleep Ray — WIS DC 16. Failure: Unconscious 1 min.\n8: Petrification Ray — CON DC 16. Two-stage Restrained → Petrified.\n9: Disintegration Ray — DEX DC 16. Failure: 36 (8d8) Force; disintegrate if reduces to 0 HP.\n10: Death Ray — DEX DC 16. Failure: 55 (10d10) Necrotic; dies if reduces to 0 HP.",
   bonusActions:"Antimagic Cone. The beholder's central eye emits an antimagic wave in a 150-foot Cone. Until start of beholder's next turn, area acts as Antimagic Field — works against beholder's own Eye Rays too.",
